Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth15. 

Know someone who would enjoy this newsletter? Send them this link! http://loox.app/ecommerce-growth-newsletter

The Micro Ambassador Program That Grew Revenue 6x in One Year​ https://www.shopify.com/blog/euphoric-herbals-micro-ambassadors

If you are not using your own customers as your brand ambassadors, you are leaving money on the table. Tune in the latest Shopify podcast to learn what is a micro ambassador program and how to identify worthy ambassadors from the founder of Euphoric Herbals.  Listen to the podcast here https://www.shopify.com/blog/euphoric-herbals-micro-ambassadors

TIP OF THE WEEK

5 Content Marketing Ideas for February 2019 https://www.practicalecommerce.com/5-content-marketing-ideas-for-february-2019

Want to increase site traffic and engage potential customers in February 2019? Consider creating articles, videos, and podcasts that entertain, inform, and just plain help out. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/5-content-marketing-ideas-for-february-2019

SHOPIFY APP OF THE WEEK

PageFly - powerful drag-and-drop page builder that boosts sales https://apps.shopify.com/pagefly?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=PageFly_Loox_partnership&utm_campaign=pagefly%2Bloox%2Bpartnership.

When it comes to building your store - powerful page builder is a must. PageFly empowers Shopify merchants to build fast-loading, high-converting storefronts.

ECOM MARKETING HACKS

Instagram’s e-commerce success is building with Stories​ https://marketingland.com/instagram-stories-the-future-of-e-commerce-254942

Here is a list of outstanding digital marketing campaigns from 2018. The campaigns include user-generated content, fake ads, specialized videos, personal stories, influencers, resolutions, and wrap-ups. Read the full article here https://marketingland.com/instagram-stories-the-future-of-e-commerce-254942

New Year, New Ecommerce Strategy https://www.business2community.com/ecommerce/new-year-new-ecommerce-strategy-02158667

With the New Year behind us and a new year in front of us, it’s time to look at ways to improve the ecommerce experience for consumers. If 2018 taught us anything, it’s that mobile and omnichannel are table stakes for merchants looking to keep customers happy and retain them over the long haul. Read the full article here https://www.business2community.com/ecommerce/new-year-new-ecommerce-strategy-02158667

How You Can Distinguish Your Dropshipping Brand by Being Social https://axcessnews.com/business/breaking-business/how-you-can-distinguish-your-dropshipping-brand-by-being-social_8368/

Much of dropshipping depends on marketing. You are competing against numerous other online retailers-some of whom may be other dropshippers selling the same products as you from the same suppliers-which means that success requires a distinguished brand.  Read the full article here https://axcessnews.com/business/breaking-business/how-you-can-distinguish-your-dropshipping-brand-by-being-social_8368/

GLOBAL TRENDS

3 Ecommerce Trends You Must Prepare for in 2019 https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/324848

The ecommerce explosion continues, but there's also an element of evolution. To take your ecommerce presence to the next level, take advantage of these emerging trends. See the full list here https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/324848

3 Strategies to Fulfill Like Amazon https://www.practicalecommerce.com/3-strategies-to-fulfill-like-amazon

If Amazon reduced shipping costs by just 1 percent, it would save $162 million. Amazon spent $16.2 billion on shipping in 2016. We can be certain that it is spending millions to improve and optimize its shipping processes. Ecommerce merchants can take advantage of Amazon’s efforts to increase profits Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/3-strategies-to-fulfill-like-amazon

column4: E- bikes order on 11/23/18 for Marcella WILSON
column6:
Dear Customer Service:

I ordered 2 E bikes from you through your advertisement on Facebook in the USA. You stated these E-bikes were easy to fold as well as reliable and hit good top speeds, and could beat weight up to 230 lb. You stated the price was reduced from $699 to $199.99 per bike on November 23, 2018. 

Therefore, I ordered 2(two) of these advertised e-bikes, and was billed $399.98 through SUPREME Q LONDON Company on that same date. Your receipt to me did not have an authorization number nor did I receive a confirming email as is the case with most reputable companies. However, I have photos of the online transaction.

It is needed by all companies, ranging from bootstrapped startups that offer coupons, to international conglomerates listed on securities exchanges. The following are recommendations based on extensive and practical experience with electronic commerce and SEO. Each of them is firmly based on careful data analysis, rather than intuitions. Read the full article here https://www.martechadvisor.com/articles/ecommerce/how-seo-is-helping-the-ecommerce-industry/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

Christmas Day is bigger than Black Friday for UK ecommerce retailers http://www.netimperative.com/2018/12/christmas-day-is-bigger-than-black-friday-for-uk-ecommerce-retailers/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

n the UK, consumers are most likely to indulge in online shopping on Christmas Day. In 2017, traffic to online retailer websites on Christmas Day was almost double (45%) the December monthly average. Three days before New Year’s Eve (28 December) purchases were more than a quarter (26%) up on the December average. Read the full article here http://www.netimperative.com/2018/12/christmas-day-is-bigger-than-black-friday-for-uk-ecommerce-retailers/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

The Indian government is playing the role of festive party pooper for Walmart and Amazon after it announced new regulations that look set to impede the U.S. duo’s efforts to grow their businesses in India. Read the full article here https://techcrunch.com/2018/12/27/amazon-walmart-india-e-commerce-restrictions/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

Peak Holiday Season Sales Up 5.1% Over 2017 https://multichannelmerchant.com/ecommerce/peak-holiday-season-sales-5-1-2017/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

Consumer confidence and fatter paychecks steamrolled right over stock market woes and a partial government shutdown, with overall peak holiday season sales excluding automobiles increasing 5.1% to $850 billion between Nov. 1 and Dec. 24, according to data from Mastercard SpendingPulse. This was the strongest growth in six years, according to Mastercard’s data, which tracks online and store sales across all payment types. Read the full article here https://multichannelmerchant.com/ecommerce/peak-holiday-season-sales-5-1-2017/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

column4: Ecom Growth: 7 conversion killers, winning SEO strategies and more
column6:
Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth13. 

Know someone who would enjoy this newsletter? Send them this link! http://loox.app/ecommerce-growth-newsletter

TOP PICK 

7 conversion snafus that kill ecommerce sales https://www.practicalecommerce.com/7-overlooked-snafus-that-kill-ecommerce-sales?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

Seemingly minor snafus in website design, wording, and navigation can drive shoppers away. Here are seven often-overlooked sales killers. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/7-overlooked-snafus-that-kill-ecommerce-sales?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

TIP OF THE WEEK

6 types of social proof and how to use trust to grow your sales​ https://loox.app/6-types-of-social-proof/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=NL_growth13&utm_term=search

Think back to the last time you ordered something from an online store. What made you click the checkout button and complete a purchase? Whether you are aware of it or not, social proof probably had something to do with it. In this post, Ruth Even Haim, the co-founder of ReConvert gives practical tips on how Shopify merchants can use the 6 types of social proof to boost your conversions. Read the full article here https://loox.app/6-types-of-social-proof/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=NL_growth13&utm_term=search

ECOM MARKETING HACKS

How 3 SEO strategies built today’s eCommerce giants https://searchengineland.com/how-3-seo-strategies-built-todays-ecommerce-giants-309321?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

Learn how third-party sellers, backlinks and a clearly defined niche can leverage SEO opportunities. Read the full article here https://searchengineland.com/how-3-seo-strategies-built-todays-ecommerce-giants-309321?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

How to get the dreaded pop-up right (& capture precious customer data) https://econsultancy.com/ecommerce-pop-up-capture-customer-data/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

the pop-up has attracted its fair share of criticism, with a reputation for being annoying, intrusive, and random – to put it nicely. This is mostly down to the “set and forget” approach that many marketers apply to data capture, displaying a pop-up as soon as a shopper lands on the website and prompting them to enter their email information. Read the full article here https://econsultancy.com/ecommerce-pop-up-capture-customer-data/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

How to use social media to get Millennials to buy from you https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/323275?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

By following these tips, you'll be sure to create a digital presence that captivates millennial consumers.  Read the full article here https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/323275?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

3 ways to narrow the mobile commerce gap https://www.practicalecommerce.com/3-ways-to-narrow-the-mobile-commerce-gap?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

A study in 2017 revealed a massive “conversion gap” on mobile. comScore found that mobile devices generated 69 percent of internet traffic but only 20 percent of ecommerce conversions. As 2018 comes to a close, has that gap changed? Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/3-ways-to-narrow-the-mobile-commerce-gap?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

THE FUTURE IS MOBILE

The Most Popular Platforms and Devices for eCommerce Sales https://priceonomics.com/the-most-popular-platforms-and-devices-for/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

Before smartphones were released over a decade ago, it hardly seemed plausible that people would actually purchase things from their phones. Mobile usage is certainly on the rise, but have ecommerce sales on mobile surpassed desktop? How popular are tablets, a more recent technology than smartphones? Which operating systems drive the most sales? Let's look at the data! https://priceonomics.com/the-most-popular-platforms-and-devices-for/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Ecom_Growth_by_Loox

column4: Ecom Growth: optimize category pages, choose a theme and more!
column6:
Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth12. 

Know someone who would enjoy this newsletter? Send them this link! http://loox.app/ecommerce-growth-newsletter

TOP PICK 

Five Common Digital Marketing Mistakes that Cost Retailers Sales this Holiday Season​ https://www.martechadvisor.com/articles/customer-experience-2/five-common-digital-marketing-mistakes-that-cost-retailers-sales-this-holiday-season/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

Based on our experience working with clients, we’ve identified five common mistakes e-commerce companies make that limit their revenue potential during this key sales period. Let’s review these along with some practical advice on how to use technology to boost your next Holiday Season sales. Read the full article here https://www.martechadvisor.com/articles/customer-experience-2/five-common-digital-marketing-mistakes-that-cost-retailers-sales-this-holiday-season/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

TIP OF THE WEEK 

Ecommerce Tips: How To Handle Post-Holiday Returns  https://www.business2community.com/ecommerce/ecommerce-tips-how-to-handle-post-holiday-returns-02147729?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

Here are some tips for merchants to get a handle on post-holiday ecommerce returns to keep customers happy and chargebacks at bay. Read the full article here https://www.business2community.com/ecommerce/ecommerce-tips-how-to-handle-post-holiday-returns-02147729?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

HOLIDAY ECOMMERCE IN NUMBERS

Holiday e‑commerce 2018 data analysis in 10 charts https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/2018/12/05/holiday-season-ecommerce-analysis/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

The stage was set for a strong online holiday season, thanks to strong e-commerce growth, national consumer confidence and consumers' willingness to buy online. These are the results of Internet Retailer's analysis of the holiday season thus far, including Thanksgiving weekend sales, consumer purchasing habits and 2018 holiday season projections. Read the full article here https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/2018/12/05/holiday-season-ecommerce-analysis/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

Toys and hobbies e-retailers’ web sales growth outpaces the broader e-commerce market https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/article/toys-and-hobbies-ecommerce-sales/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

Toys and hobbies retailers collectively grew their online sales 21.5% in 2017—the fourth-fastest rate among the 15 product categories tracked by Internet Retailer. Read the full article here https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/article/toys-and-hobbies-ecommerce-sales/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

Cyber Monday 2018 Is the New Day to Beat in Ecommerce https://www.adweek.com/digital/cyber-monday-2018-is-the-new-day-to-beat-in-ecommerce/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

U.S. consumers spent $7.9 billion online on Cyber Monday 2018, officially making it the new reigning champ of U.S. ecommerce and topping the 2017 record of $6.6 billion by more than 19 percent. Read the full article here https://www.adweek.com/digital/cyber-monday-2018-is-the-new-day-to-beat-in-ecommerce/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

GLOBAL TRENDS

Why 2018 Was the ‘Year of Ecommerce’ in Southeast Asia https://www.adweek.com/digital/why-2018-was-the-year-of-ecommerce-in-southeast-asia/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

The digital economy in Southeast Asia is on track to hit $240 billion by 2025, which is $40 billion more than previous estimates, according to the latest e-Conomy Southeast Asia 2018 report from Google and Singapore-based Temasek, which manages investments and assets for the government. Read the full article here https://www.adweek.com/digital/why-2018-was-the-year-of-ecommerce-in-southeast-asia/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

EU ends geoblocking in ecommerce https://ecommercenews.eu/eu-ends-geoblocking-in-ecommerce/

The European Union has called an end to geoblocking for online shoppers. This means that ecommerce websites in the EU can no longer block visitors from other EU countries. The new law has come into force this week. Read the full article https://ecommercenews.eu/eu-ends-geoblocking-in-ecommerce/

ECOMMERCE MARKETING 

The potential of community and technology in ecommerce https://venturebeat.com/2018/12/04/the-potential-of-community-and-technology-in-ecommerce/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

The community effect has great potential in the ecommerce space. As ecommerce grows by 15 percent year-over-year, community-powered technologies can help the industry grow sustainably while providing better information, stronger connections, and more ways to participate.  Read the full article here https://venturebeat.com/2018/12/04/the-potential-of-community-and-technology-in-ecommerce/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

Creating a Content Marketing Strategy for Ecommerce https://www.practicalecommerce.com/creating-a-content-marketing-strategy-for-ecommerce?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

A clear content marketing strategy defines its purpose, who it serves, and its format. A company selling an expensive, unfamiliar, or complex product may want to move potential customers through the sales cycle. Content that answers questions or concerns might help. Start your company’s content marketing strategy with goals, and document them. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/creating-a-content-marketing-strategy-for-ecommerce?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

SEO: 6 Ways to Optimize Category Pages https://www.practicalecommerce.com/seo-6-ways-to-optimize-category-pages?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

By adding features that increase engagement and conversion, optimizing the accompanying text, and, yes, adding some well-placed body copy, your category pages will better communicate their relevance to search engines to attract more shoppers. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/seo-6-ways-to-optimize-category-pages?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

How to choose the right Shopify theme for your online store https://www.besttechie.com/how-to-choose-the-right-shopify-theme-for-your-online-store/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

Choosing a theme for your store is one of the first steps during setup. It sets the tone for your store and speaks volumes about the purpose of your store. The perfect theme can go a long way in getting your web store noticed by millions of people who make online purchases every day. Read on to know more about the themes offered by Shopify. Read the full article here https://www.besttechie.com/how-to-choose-the-right-shopify-theme-for-your-online-store/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

TOP VIDEO

In this video by Kevin David you learn how to create Facebook Ad Copy and Images that convert! You will also learn how to find profitable ads that you can use as inspiration and  go over tons of examples! This video is a step-by-step Facebook marketing tutorial.

See the full video here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5C5QMSfmJjc&list=PLf273XQ3EUQmgpcPYoHBOcppiHHCbIq1k&utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=Looxgrowth&utm_term=looxgrowthnewsletter

Know someone who would enjoy this newsletter? Send them this link! http://loox.app/ecommerce-growth-newsletter

Thanks for your time, tune in again next week.

Yoni Elbaz, Co-founder & CEO at Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth12

Yoni from Loox

With the intense level of competition you’ll find in the e-commerce space, it’s quite easy for your store to get overlooked. Fortunately, I’ve found that certain strategies, when paired with sound business planning, will help you stand out from the competition. Read the full article here https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbescommunicationscouncil/2018/11/29/four-tips-for-competing-in-crowded-e-commerce-product-niches/#74a303346668

SEO FOR ECOMMERCE

Assessing the ROI of SEO for eCommerce Websites https://www.goinflow.com/roi-of-seo/?utm_source=looxgrowthnewsletter

t is easier than you think to estimate the ROI of SEO improvements for eCommerce websites. In this article, we’re going to show you how we do it. Read the full article here https://www.goinflow.com/roi-of-seo/?utm_source=looxgrowthnewsletter

Why SEO is so beneficial for any eCommerce business https://www.seoshark.com.au/why-seo-is-so-beneficial-for-any-ecommerce-business/

The eCommerce industry has seen some exciting changes in 2018 and has provided some great prospects looking forward. Electronic commerce refers to the commercial transactions carried out over electronic networks, predominantly the internet. What’s so great about it at this point in time?  Read the full article here https://www.seoshark.com.au/why-seo-is-so-beneficial-for-any-ecommerce-business/

Why good content marketing strategies is the key for your eCommerce success https://www.techgenyz.com/2018/11/21/content-marketing-strategy-ecommerce-success/

Aside from using SEO tactics that will optimize your store to appeal to the search engine gods, content creation, as a significant part of digital marketing strategy, will be the determining factor between a thriving online store and a deserted website. Here’s what you need to know. Read the full article here https://www.techgenyz.com/2018/11/21/content-marketing-strategy-ecommerce-success/

BUSINESS STRATEGY

Building an Ecommerce Business, Part 7: Shipping and Fulfillment https://www.practicalecommerce.com/building-an-ecommerce-business-part-7-shipping-and-fulfillment

A merchant who sells physical products has to figure out how to efficiently get those items into the hands of customers. It can become complicated as the business scales and receives international orders. This is episode seven in my series on building an ecommerce business from the ground up. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/building-an-ecommerce-business-part-7-shipping-and-fulfillment

E-commerce logistics: how to make money from free shipping https://theloadstar.co.uk/e-commerce-logistics-make-money-free-shipping/

A recent survey of 1,508 online shoppers, published by Convey, a provider of a cloud-based delivery experience platform used by a number of large shippers, found that expectations regarding punctuality and convenience had gone up. Consumers expect fast, free shipping with full control over the experience, the survey concluded. Read the full article https://theloadstar.co.uk/e-commerce-logistics-make-money-free-shipping/

A Year-round Cash Strategy for Ecommerce https://www.practicalecommerce.com/a-year-round-cash-strategy-for-ecommerce-sellers

Merchants need a cash strategy now. In this post, I’ll outline a five-step process to calculate your year-long cash needs, manage incoming cash, and reward yourself..  Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/a-year-round-cash-strategy-for-ecommerce-sellers

GLOBAL TRENDS

Ecommerce challenges in 2018 & beyond https://www.retailgazette.co.uk/blog/2018/11/comment-the-ecommerce-challenges-of-2018-beyond/

We’ve spoken to a range of ecommerce business owners to get their thoughts on what challenges they face now and what they expect to be tackling in the years to come. Read the full article here https://www.retailgazette.co.uk/blog/2018/11/comment-the-ecommerce-challenges-of-2018-beyond/

INTERVIEWS

Milk Bottle Labs Podcast Episode 3: Photo Reviews https://milkbottlelabs.com/blogs/news/podcast-episode-3-photo-reviews-with-yoni-from-loox-io

Let me start by saying, a large number of customer interactions is a nice problem to have. In our world, customer interaction means they are into your offering, and the equation is simple – a lot of customer questions = a lot of sales. But in order to make every interaction count, and make every shopper a permanent one, some groundwork needs to be done. Read the full article here https://sallybot.com/customer-service-blog/5-tips-to-boost-customer-service-towards-hollidays-season/?utm_source=Loox&utm_medium=Newsletter&utm_campaign=hollidays-season

TIP OF THE WEEK 

5 innovative ways to use product reviews to increase your BFCM sales https://loox.app/5-innovative-ways-to-use-product-reviews-to-increase-your-bfcm-sales/

You already have your BFCM strategy in place, but here is something that probably slipped your mind. We offer you five innovative ways to use reviews and user-generated content that will take your store to the top. Read the full article here https://loox.app/5-innovative-ways-to-use-product-reviews-to-increase-your-bfcm-sales/

MARKETING

The ultimate guide to Instagram for small ecommerce brands https://thenextweb.com/contributors/2018/11/19/the-ultimate-guide-to-instagram-for-small-ecommerce-brands/

The release of shoppable posts has now afforded ecommerce companies the luxury of tagging products within an individual image, so that users can tap a product and be sent straight to the “add to cart” section on the ecommerce site. It seems that the days of “shop via link in bio” might soon be a thing of the past…Read the full article here https://thenextweb.com/contributors/2018/11/19/the-ultimate-guide-to-instagram-for-small-ecommerce-brands/

5 ways ecommerce brands create strong communities https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/323352

Consumers have their pick of online retail sites. Make yours irresistible to even the most skeptical of the bunch by forging a tight-knit community of brand supporters. Read the full article here https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/323352

An email list isn’t just for emailing https://www.practicalecommerce.com/an-email-list-isnt-just-for-emailing

The best email lists contain more info than addresses. Tools such as MailChimp are immensely powerful and can serve as a secondary analytics source, depending on what you track. Thus an email list can be a detailed customer file.  Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/an-email-list-isnt-just-for-emailing

Building an ecommerce business, part 6: hiring employees https://www.practicalecommerce.com/building-an-ecommerce-business-part-6-hiring-employees

Employees are a company’s greatest asset. Without the right people, a new ecommerce business would almost certainly fail. Refining the hiring process can help find the perfect candidate and reduce the amount of time wasted for all parties. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/building-an-ecommerce-business-part-6-hiring-employees

GLOBAL TRENDS

Turning the tide: the eco-box ecommerce rethink https://packagingeurope.com/tide-procter-gamble-ecobox-ecommerce-packaging/

Many of the most audacious recent innovations in packaging have been driven by the demands of online retail, as the model begins to mature and industry works out the requirements and pitfalls of its extended and bumpy supply chains. Read the full article here https://packagingeurope.com/tide-procter-gamble-ecobox-ecommerce-packaging/

The future of ecommerce and retail will be written in China https://www.forbes.com/sites/oppenheimerfunds/2018/11/15/the-future-of-e-commerce-and-retail-will-be-written-in-china/#16358f6a115f

China's experiments in shopping are moving into high gear. The world needs to pay attention. Read the full article here https://www.forbes.com/sites/oppenheimerfunds/2018/11/15/the-future-of-e-commerce-and-retail-will-be-written-in-china/#16358f6a115f

NEWS

Chinese e-commerce sites ditch Dolce & Gabbana in ad backlash​ https://www.investing.com/news/technology-news/chinese-ecommerce-sites-ditch-dolce--gabbana-in-ad-backlash-1697785

D&G goods disappeared from Chinese e-commerce platforms on Wednesday. Read the full article here https://www.investing.com/news/technology-news/chinese-ecommerce-sites-ditch-dolce--gabbana-in-ad-backlash-1697785

Shopify goes shopping; Swedish DIY e-commerce startup Tictail to fold into its bigger rival https://tech.eu/brief/shopify-tictail/

Tictail, the Swedish tech company that offers a combination between a DIY e-commerce platform and a social shopping experience for buyers, has been acquired by its much larger, publicly-listed competitor Shopify. Read the full article here https://tech.eu/brief/shopify-tictail/

INSPIRATION

The challenges of a young ecommerce founder https://www.techinasia.com/challenges-young-ecommerce-founder

“I didn’t have any mentors to guide me on how to run an ecommerce business. I couldn’t even refer to online courses because most of them catered to US or European markets, which don’t rely on cash-on-delivery payment,” he recalls. Not one to be discouraged, Lagazo went all in and quit his sales job. In January 2018, he launched Medusa Luxuries, an online retailer of affordable jewelry. Read the full article here https://www.techinasia.com/challenges-young-ecommerce-founder

Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth8. 

Know someone who would enjoy this newsletter? Send them this link! http://loox.app/ecommerce-growth-newsletter

TOP PICK 

What We Learned from Assessing over a Million Ecommerce Websites https://medium.com/@proonto/you-have-a-1-102-chance-to-grow-your-ecommerce-business-to-7-figures-new-data-suggests-cc2fe6361b19

You Have a 1:102 Chance to Grow your Ecommerce Business to 7 figures, New Data Suggests. So what do successful 7 figure stores have in common?  Read the full article here https://medium.com/@proonto/you-have-a-1-102-chance-to-grow-your-ecommerce-business-to-7-figures-new-data-suggests-cc2fe6361b19

TIP OF THE WEEK 

5 Ecommerce Marketing Trends to Watch in 2019 https://www.practicalecommerce.com/5-ecommerce-marketing-trends-to-watch-in-2019

In 2019, you’ll likely hear about artificial intelligence, influencer marketing, virtual reality, and any number of other marketing and advertising possibilities. But some may be a few years from having an impact. So what about something a bit more practical? Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/5-ecommerce-marketing-trends-to-watch-in-2019

HOLIDAY SEARSON

Alibaba's Singles Day made e-commerce history — but the numbers also suggest China's economy is cooling down https://www.businessinsider.com/alibaba-stock-price-singles-day-historical-ecommerce-china-eco-cools-down-2018-11

Alibaba reported that customers spent $30.8 billion in 24 hours, a significant increase from the $25.3 billion in gross merchandise volume (GMV) Alibaba shoppers spent in 2017. That was almost three times the amount of last year's Black Friday and Cyber Monday sales combined. Read the full article here https://www.businessinsider.com/alibaba-stock-price-singles-day-historical-ecommerce-china-eco-cools-down-2018-11

YOUR 7-POINT BLACK FRIDAY CHECKLIST FOR PAID SEARCH https://www.clickthrough-marketing.com/blog/your-7-point-black-friday-checklist-for-paid-search

So, how have you been preparing for this year's Black Friday bonanza? Read on to discover top tips on shaping your Black Friday campaigns for success: Read the full article here https://www.clickthrough-marketing.com/blog/your-7-point-black-friday-checklist-for-paid-search

Black Friday predictions from UK retail experts https://www.retail-insight-network.com/features/black-friday-predictions/

UK consumers are expected to spend almost £5bn on black Friday this year, with half of this expected to be spent online. Experts share their Black Friday predictions. Read the full article here. Read the full article here https://www.retail-insight-network.com/features/black-friday-predictions/

MARKETING

What brands can do to improve ecommerce performance https://www.clickz.com/how-to-improve-ecommerce-performance/220283/

Tip #1: optimize your product display pages (PDPs) across non-Amazon retailers. 38% of consumers said they'd leave a site from lack of product content. Read the full article here https://www.clickz.com/how-to-improve-ecommerce-performance/220283/

16 Quick and Free Grammar and Usage Resources https://www.practicalecommerce.com/16-quick-and-free-grammar-and-usage-resources

At 3 a.m., while polishing an email blast for your customers, you get a brain freeze about a grammar question. For instance: Should it be “their’s,” “they’res,” “there’s,” or “theirs”? Which punctuation mark (if any) does a certain sentence need in the middle? Do we capitalize “French” in “French cuffs”? Use the free online resources below to answer such questions quickly. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/16-quick-and-free-grammar-and-usage-resources

I http://middlemarketgrowth.org/protecting-brand-in-age-of-ecommerce/n an Age of E-Commerce Behemoths, Brand Is Worth Fighting to Protect http://middlemarketgrowth.org/protecting-brand-in-age-of-ecommerce/

n the age of giant online retailers, it’s not easy being a specialty brand or brick-and-mortar store. Do you throw your lot in with the likes of Amazon, expanding your retail availability and risk losing pricing power, brand cache and, possibly, consumer loyalty? What we can learn from Walmart’s misadventure with acquiring the outdoor e-commerce marketplace Moosejaw. Read the full article here http://middlemarketgrowth.org/protecting-brand-in-age-of-ecommerce/

Four E-Commerce SEO Trends To Prepare For In 2019 https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbesagencycouncil/2018/11/02/four-e-commerce-seo-trends-to-prepare-for-in-2019/#5bc2b93d3232

it’s important to maintain a firm grasp on the latest e-commerce SEO trends as they emerge and leverage them so you can start 2019 at the top. Read the full article here https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbesagencycouncil/2018/11/02/four-e-commerce-seo-trends-to-prepare-for-in-2019/#5bc2b93d3232

INSPIRATION

Overcoming Fear of Failure in Ecommerce https://billionaire365.com/2018/11/12/overcoming-fear-of-failure-in-ecommerce/

Overcoming fear of failure in ecommerce is something every online entrepreneur has to grapple with at some point. Your best chance, whether you’re launching ebooks online stores, a new software platform or the next eBay is to stop tripping and get at it. Here’s how others have done so. I received my solar panel yesterday.  To say I was disappointed is beyond description.  Your "1050 * 540 * 2.5mm/41.3 X 21.2 X 1 inch" (taken directly from your advertisement) is only 228 * 127 mm.  I am contacting my credit card company to cancel this payment as fraud unless I (1) hear from you immediately and (2) a panel that fits the advertised description is sent to me.  Please find attached the relevant parts of your advertisement and a photo of what you actually sent me.
Don Stacks

column4:
Ecom Growth: $1 Trillion Christmas, retain holiday shoppers,
 attribute sales and more!
column6:
Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth7. 

Know someone who would enjoy this newsletter? Send them this link! http://loox.app/ecommerce-growth-newsletter

TOP PICK 

This will be a $1 trillion Christmas, thanks to e-commerce https://www.techradar.com/news/this-will-be-a-dollar1-trillion-christmas-thanks-to-e-commerce

Black Friday and Cyber Monday 2018 will be massive. Read the full article here https://www.techradar.com/news/this-will-be-a-dollar1-trillion-christmas-thanks-to-e-commerce

TIP OF THE WEEK 

Retain the Shopify Customers You Attract this Peak Shopping Season https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/322866

The coming weeks will be full of parties, gifts and friends. But don't let another 'gift' slip through your fingers: a customer who's here to stay. Read the full article here https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/322866

ANALYTICS FOR ECOMMERCE

How ecommerce marketers can get started with attribution https://econsultancy.com/three-things-e-commerce-marketers-can-do-to-measure-attribution/

Attribution was already a tricky piece of analysis, but with GDPR it’s become that bit harder – there are now additional barriers to obtaining Google and Facebook data in your log-files. And the dedicated tools that you can buy are expensive and complex to set up and use. However, all is not lost. There’s a lot you can still do to push forward your deeper measurement plans. Here’s three things you can do. Read the full article here https://econsultancy.com/three-things-e-commerce-marketers-can-do-to-measure-attribution/

How to Audit Google Analytics Data, for Ecommerce https://www.practicalecommerce.com/how-to-audit-google-analytics-data-for-ecommerce

Data from Google Analytics helps ecommerce merchants make key decisions. But that assumes the data is accurate. In this post, I’ll provide instructions for conducting a Google Analytics audit to confirm the accuracy of the data or identify potential errors. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/how-to-audit-google-analytics-data-for-ecommerce

MARKETING

5 Impactful Areas to Focus for Successful E-Commerce Entrepreneurship https://www.influencive.com/5-impactful-areas-to-focus-for-successful-e-commerce-entrepreneurship/

If you are aiming to build a winning e-commerce business model, focusing on the following critical areas will give you a guaranteed success. Read the full article here https://www.influencive.com/5-impactful-areas-to-focus-for-successful-e-commerce-entrepreneurship/

5 Simple Ways to Boost Conversions https://www.practicalecommerce.com/5-simple-ways-to-boost-conversions

When it comes to increasing conversions of an online store, big retailers have money and brand recognition. Smaller ecommerce sites have to focus on more down-to-earth tactics. Here are five ways to improve on-site conversions without breaking the bank. Read the full article here http://www.fourthsource.com/branding/brand-storytelling-how-to-leverage-it-effectively-to-boost-sales-23280

INSPIRATION

20 Modern, Clean Ecommerce Sites, for Inspiration https://www.practicalecommerce.com/20-modern-clean-ecommerce-sites-for-inspiration

A clean, modern design can be effective for an ecommerce store. It prevents shoppers from being overwhelmed with excessive content, confusing menus, and aggressive sales promotions — allowing stores to create sales through a focus on products. Here is a collection of clean, modern ecommerce sites. There are fashion sites, specialty boutiques, and design-focused brands. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/20-modern-clean-ecommerce-sites-for-inspiration

Starting An E-Commerce Store? These Five Industries Are Ripe For Big Profits https://www.forbes.com/sites/theyec/2018/11/05/starting-an-e-commerce-store-these-five-industries-are-ripe-for-big-profits/#2be2554cd7d8

If you’re looking to become an internet entrepreneur, you may be tempted to get into e-commerce. After all, it’s easier than ever today with simple website templates, third-party fulfillment and the ability to sell inventory that you never even buy until you make your first sale. If you’re interested in e-commerce, here are five fabulous niches that are ready for big profits: Read the full article here https://www.forbes.com/sites/theyec/2018/11/05/starting-an-e-commerce-store-these-five-industries-are-ripe-for-big-profits/#2be2554cd7d8

HOLIDAY SEASON

10 Strategies To Get Your E-Commerce Site Ready For The Holiday Rush https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbestechcouncil/2018/11/07/10-strategies-to-get-your-e-commerce-site-ready-for-the-holiday-rush/#4e7dc9af7cda

We asked 10 Forbes Technology Council members to share their advice for preparing for the holiday season.  Read the full article here https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbestechcouncil/2018/11/07/10-strategies-to-get-your-e-commerce-site-ready-for-the-holiday-rush/#4e7dc9af7cda

Holiday Social Media Tips for Fashion, Lifestyle Merchants https://www.practicalecommerce.com/holiday-social-media-tips-for-fashion-lifestyle-merchants

Social media helps current and prospective customers feel valued, appreciated, and informed. It instills trust. To entice holiday shoppers to come to a smaller store instead of, say, a leading brand, go the extra mile — from product selection to customer service to marketing, including unique social media campaigns. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/holiday-social-media-tips-for-fashion-lifestyle-merchants

Singles’ Day, the shopping event that makes Black Friday look like a yard sale https://www.abacusnews.com/who-what/singles-day-shopping-event-makes-black-friday-look-yard-sale/article/2172101

November 11 is China’s Singles’ Day, a national online shopping feast. Started by Alibaba in 2009, its sales volume now is bigger than Black Friday and Cyber Monday combined. Read the full article here https://www.abacusnews.com/who-what/singles-day-shopping-event-makes-black-friday-look-yard-sale/article/2172101

ECOSYSTEM

New head of eBay Seller Experiences details major changes https://www.ecommercebytes.com/C/blog/blog.pl?/pl/2018/11/1541640735.html

eBay's new Vice President of Seller Experience Harry Temkin revealed in an interview on Wednesday changes that will be coming to the marketplace and described how they will impact sellers. Read the full article here https://www.ecommercebytes.com/C/blog/blog.pl?/pl/2018/11/1541640735.html

'Free shipping is pretty much table stakes' in e-commerce today, Etsy CEO says https://www.cnbc.com/2018/11/07/etsy-ceo-free-shipping-is-pretty-much-table-stakes-in-e-commerce.html

E-commerce companies are under pressure to offer free shipping from deal-chasing consumers, and those who don't may run the risk of falling behind their competitors, Etsy President and CEO Josh Silverman said Wednesday. Read the full article here https://www.cnbc.com/2018/11/07/etsy-ceo-free-shipping-is-pretty-much-table-stakes-in-e-commerce.html

TOP TWEET

https://twitter.com/i_sajjadshahid/status/1059429022495662080

TOP VIDEO

In this video, Tristan Broughton explains the differences between Google Ads vs Facebook Ads. Recommended for those who are new to the world of online advertising!

See the full video here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y5HAisEunW0

column4: 3 tips for effective product videos, shoppable Snapchat ads and more!
column6:
Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth6. 

TOP PICK 

Here's How Your Brand Can Make The Most Of User-Generated Content https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbescommunicationscouncil/2018/10/31/heres-how-your-brand-can-make-the-most-of-user-generated-content/#6ddc19527668

With such a high demand for unique, engaging content, it can be overwhelming for brands to keep delivering what their target market wants. One simple strategy that many businesses have adopted is to take advantage of user-generated content (UGC). Read the full article here https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbescommunicationscouncil/2018/10/31/heres-how-your-brand-can-make-the-most-of-user-generated-content/#6ddc19527668

TIP OF THE WEEK 

3 Tips to Create Effective Product Videos for an eCommerce Website https://esellercafe.com/3-tips-to-create-effective-product-videos-for-an-ecommerce-website/

Ecommerce videos are as hot as ever. While looking at examples of product videos for inspiration may help, often it won’t cut it. Instead you could try using the following tips to come up with much more effective product videos. Read the full article here https://esellercafe.com/3-tips-to-create-effective-product-videos-for-an-ecommerce-website/

MARKETING

Shoppable Ads Give Ecommerce Businesses a New Way to Promote on Snapchat https://smallbiztrends.com/2018/10/snapchat-shoppable-ads.html

The key to making your ad dollars count on Snapchat is knowing your audience. While Facebook and Instagram have more monthly users, Snapchat can deliver influencers with niche markets that are affordable. Read the full article here https://smallbiztrends.com/2018/10/snapchat-shoppable-ads.html

Brand Storytelling: How to Leverage it Effectively to Boost Sales http://www.fourthsource.com/branding/brand-storytelling-how-to-leverage-it-effectively-to-boost-sales-23280

Storytelling can prove to be an effective tool to improve conversions. As per a research, if people like a brand story, 55% are more likely to buy the product in the future, 44% will share the story, and 15% will buy the product immediately. Read the full article here http://www.fourthsource.com/branding/brand-storytelling-how-to-leverage-it-effectively-to-boost-sales-23280

STRATEGY 

4 Warning Signs Your E-commerce Idea Is Failed From the Start https://www.business.com/articles/bad-ecommerce-business-idea-warning-signs/

A lot of e-commerce stores are opening these days, but most of them fail because the core idea behind them isn't appealing to their audience. Below are four warning signs that your e-commerce idea needs to be retooled in order to be successful in the long run. Read the full article here https://www.business.com/articles/bad-ecommerce-business-idea-warning-signs/

[AUDIO] https://www.practicalecommerce.com/building-an-ecommerce-business-part-1-choosing-partnersBuilding an Ecommerce Business, Part 4: Copywriting Matters​ https://www.practicalecommerce.com/building-an-ecommerce-business-part-4-copywriting-matters

In this podcast series, the founder of Beardbrand, an Austin, Texas-based ecommerce business that focuses on beard care and men’s grooming hosts audio interviews for the “Ecommerce Conversations” podcast. The podcast covers a wide range of topics around anything that helps fellow merchants.  In this fourth installment in my series of conversations about building an ecommerce business, I visited with Neville Medhora, founder of Kopywriting Kourse. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/building-an-ecommerce-business-part-1-choosing-partners

BFCM AND HOLIDAY SEASON

6 Holiday Ecommerce Shipping Mistakes to Avoid​ https://www.practicalecommerce.com/6-holiday-ecommerce-shipping-mistakes-to-avoid

Customers expect delivery. For online stores that sell tangible products, order fulfillment is arguably the single most essential task. It is the culmination of marketing, web development, and customer service. For retail ecommerce businesses, providing a customer with a product is the mission. And the worst possible time to mess up that mission could be during the peak holiday sales season.Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/6-holiday-ecommerce-shipping-mistakes-to-avoid

5 Tips to Boost Your Ecommerce Sales on Cyber Monday https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/321928

Your goal should be to make your deals too good to resist. Is 50 percent off too high? Probably. Of course, it can be difficult to get noticed on Cyber Monday with so many knockout deals offered by big-box stores. Consider instituting the following five tips to boost your ecommerce sales on Cyber Monday. Read the full article here https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/321928

TRENDS

The Future Trends of eCommerce (infographic)​ https://www.digitalinformationworld.com/2018/10/infographic-future-ecommerce-stats-and-trends.html

According to predictions, "By the end of 2018, the global eCommerce sales will reach approximately $2.8 trillion and in 2021 it will hit $4.5 trillion. With eCommerce evolving at a rapid pace, it can be hard to keep up with the latest trends." This infographic created by Subscriptionly, illustrates 60 statistics and insights that will design the future of eCommerce. Read the full article here https://www.digitalinformationworld.com/2018/10/infographic-future-ecommerce-stats-and-trends.html

5 Ways Ecommerce Brands Should Approach Content Marketing https://www.searchenginejournal.com/ecommerce-brands-content-marketing/274393/

The harsh reality is that some strategies can work like magic one day, then be completely obsolete the next. Nowadays, the scope of what defines “good content” for ecommerce businesses is a layered concept that involves many elements. Let’s discuss five ways ecommerce brands can establish themselves as a force to be reckoned with. Read the full article here https://www.searchenginejournal.com/ecommerce-brands-content-marketing/274393/

Online returns in Europe https://ecommercenews.eu/online-returns-in-europe/

Any customer who bought a product online, has the right to return this item. In Europe, online consumers have the right to cancel and return their order within 14 days. They don’t need to tell the retailer why they are returning the item. What are the rules regarding returns for retailers? Read the full article here https://ecommercenews.eu/online-returns-in-europe/

https://twitter.com/VladoBotsvadze/status/1057317687381114880/photo/1

TOP VIDEO

In this video, Arie Scherson talk sabout the easiest way to start a profitable Shopify dropshipping store in 2019. 

See the full video here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GUuxOQoDrSc

I am very dissappointed with your way to handle your shipments.
When placing my order in october the 4th, I upgraded my order to 3-7 business days AND PAID FOR THAT PRIORITY TREATMENT!
I am still waiting for the delivery.
Even if - as I saw - the package is in Luxembourg right now and you might not be able to speed up the delivery process from where ever you are I really feel cheated by you. How can you promise extra short delivery time and take money for a promise you cannot keep?

I expect a very good explanation from you.
The least you should do is to pay back for the delivery upgrade.

I really hope that the goods I purchased is better than the way you sell your stuff.

With sad regards,

Christian von Bennigsen

column4: 5 ways eCommerce will change in 2019, personalization, visual search and more
column6:
Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth6. 

TOP PICK 

How Ecommerce Websites Can Achieve E-A-T Quality https://www.searchenginejournal.com/ecommerce-websites-expertise-authority-trust/273111/

When Google updated their Search Quality Rater Guidelines in July this year, the concept of E-A-T (Expertise, Authority, Trust) gained spotlight once again.   For ecommerce websites, achieving E-A-T is a balance of optimizing page formats and content design for conversion and achieving the necessary on-page signals that Google is looking for. Read the full article here https://www.searchenginejournal.com/ecommerce-websites-expertise-authority-trust/273111/

TIP OF THE WEEK 

Personalizing the eCommerce Shopping Experience for More Sales https://www.business2community.com/ecommerce/personalizing-the-ecommerce-shopping-experience-for-more-sales-02130683 

To the uninitiated, their decision to maximize traffic — any traffic — at all costs seems like a legit game plan. After all, with traffic comes leads and sales, right? There is some truth to that, of course. However, there’s an even better approach. And that is, focus on getting traffic from a specific group of people. Those that have a high probability of converting. Read the full article here https://www.business2community.com/ecommerce/personalizing-the-ecommerce-shopping-experience-for-more-sales-02130683

GLOBAL STRATEGY 

The 20 Best Team Management Apps for Small Businesses https://smallbiztrends.com/2018/10/best-team-management-apps.html

For businesses with small teams, keeping employees active and on top of their daily tasks is absolutely essential. Meetings and constant email chains can lead to a lot of wasted time, so having an app that’s specifically geared toward managing your team can be a huge benefit.  Read the full article here https://smallbiztrends.com/2018/10/best-team-management-apps.html

Shopify deal could see eBay add thousands of sellers https://www.insideretail.com.au/news/ebay-partners-with-shopify-to-expand-seller-network-201810

EBay Australia has partnered with popular e-commerce platform, Shopify, to make it easier for users to list and sell their products through the online marketplace. ​ Read the full article here https://www.insideretail.com.au/news/ebay-partners-with-shopify-to-expand-seller-network-201810

TRENDS

5 ways e-commerce will change in 2019 https://www.afr.com/technology/web/ecommerce/5-ways-ecommerce-will-change-in-2019-20181024-h171ir

Retailers must adapt to the changing needs of the consumer and e-commerce landscape in order to remain competitive. So with 2017/18 behind us, let's take a look at what the coming year could bring. Read the full article here https://www.afr.com/technology/web/ecommerce/5-ways-ecommerce-will-change-in-2019-20181024-h171ir

Visual Search Speaks Loud And Clear For Ecommerce https://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/327064/visual-search-speaks-loud-and-clear-for-ecommerce.html

Aaron Kessler, Raymond James analyst, in a research report released Wednesday wrote how companies like Alibaba, Amazon, eBay, Facebook, Google, Houzz, Pinterest, and Wayfair continue to move toward offering visual search for ecommerce. So if your ecommerce brand is still not on Pinterest - the time is now. Read the full article here https://www.mediapost.com/publications/article/327064/visual-search-speaks-loud-and-clear-for-ecommerce.html

SECURITY

eCommerce Profit Parasites Leech Revenues and Mislead Results https://www.prweb.com/releases/ecommerce_profit_parasites_leech_revenues_and_mislead_results/prweb15865365.htm

62% of merchants cite chargebacks as top benchmark for fraud, but many overlook their impact on revenue. Writing off chargebacks, returns, refunds and other losses as a cost of doing business can be very misleading, essentially resulting in ‘fake’ revenue that creates a false sense of security. Loss prevention specialist Chargebacks911 examines how profit parasites skew financial results and threaten eCommerce sustainability. Read the full article here https://www.prweb.com/releases/ecommerce_profit_parasites_leech_revenues_and_mislead_results/prweb15865365.htm

The Invisible Ecommerce Thief: Online Journey Hijacking http://www.econtentmag.com/Articles/Editorial/Industry-Insights/The-Invisible-Ecommerce-Thief-Online-Journey-Hijacking-128082.htm

Through analyzing hundreds of millions of websites, it has been determined that 15% to 25% (and up to 30% during the peak holiday season) of online shoppers are victims of Online Journey Hijacking. These shoppers are encountering unauthorized, malware-driven advertisements when shopping online–including product and banner ads, pop-ups and other injected content, disrupting the seamless customer experience brands strive to deliver.​​ Read the full article here http://www.econtentmag.com/Articles/Editorial/Industry-Insights/The-Invisible-Ecommerce-Thief-Online-Journey-Hijacking-128082.htm

FULLFILMENT

This Is the Unexpected Side Effect of Booming Online Sales https://footwearnews.com/2018/business/retail/retail-warehouse-space-online-sales-ecommerce-1202695581/

While some retailers are still struggling to navigate the digital landscape, others who do have a grasp on e-commerce are continuing to see sales on the rise. But an unexpected side effect to this digital boom has materialized: a shrinking number of available warehouse spaces and increasingly inundated U.S. distribution centers. Read the full article here https://footwearnews.com/2018/business/retail/retail-warehouse-space-online-sales-ecommerce-1202695581/

Facing the challenge of product returns in eCommerce https://www.enterprisetimes.co.uk/2018/10/25/facing-the-challenge-of-product-returns-in-ecommerce/

New research from Brightpearl, reveals that nearly half (45%) of retailers are planning to ban ‘serial returners.’ A move that could see shoppers abandon their favourite brands in droves.  Read the full article here https://www.enterprisetimes.co.uk/2018/10/25/facing-the-challenge-of-product-returns-in-ecommerce/

8 Things You Need to Consider When Choosing an E-Commerce Fulfillment Company https://uk.pcmag.com/business/85524/8-things-you-need-to-consider-when-choosing-an-e-commerce-fu

Companies such as 3dcart and Shopify, both of which provide e-commerce software to online merchants, also integrate directly with third-party e-commerce fulfillment services, such as eFulfillment Services (EFS) or Fulfillify. Although this arrangement is one way to manage fulfillment, it's by no means the only way. Read the full article here https://uk.pcmag.com/business/85524/8-things-you-need-to-consider-when-choosing-an-e-commerce-fu

TOP TWEET

https://twitter.com/EU_Commission/status/1054726594336604162

TOP VIDEO

So you think you've found your winning product... have you REALLY? In this video, Rito from Flying Start Online explores a recent experiment he did and how FAILING RAPIDLY can help you find your next winning product.

See the full video here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EG_48-8xA88

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EG_48-8xA88

Know someone who would enjoy this newsletter? Send them this link! http://loox.app/ecommerce-growth-newsletter

Thanks for your time, tune in again next week.

Yoni Elbaz, Co-founder & CEO at Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth6

Yoni from Loox

column4:
Facebook Video losing traction,
 what 88% of stores get wrong with analytics and more!
column6:
Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth5. 

TOP PICK 

Facebook Video Losing Traction Among Users​ https://www.mediaplaynews.com/ampere-facebook-video-losing-traction-among-users/

Despite a monthly global users base around 2 billion, Facebook users aren’t streaming much video, according to new data from Ampere Analysis. The London-based research firm found that video streaming among Facebook users in the United States dropped to less than a quarter (23.7%) in the third quarter of 2018, compared to 35.5% in Q3 2016. Read the full article here https://www.mediaplaynews.com/ampere-facebook-video-losing-traction-among-users/

TIP OF THE WEEK 

88% of Shopify stores have Google Analytics set up incorrectly https://econsultancy.com/shopify-stores-google-analytics-set-up-incorrectly/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=loox&utm_campaign=ecommercegrowthnewsletterbyloox

Online marketers are spending billions of dollars to acquire traffic for these stores, but there is a big problem: the Google Analytics setup for most stores is broken. Littledata looked at 590 Shopify stores who ran our free Google Analytics audit, but didn’t opt to fix issues. We found that just 70 sites had all of the ecommerce data tracked correctly in Google Analytics. The other 420 stores had serious issues.  Read the full article here https://econsultancy.com/shopify-stores-google-analytics-set-up-incorrectly/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_medium=loox&utm_campaign=ecommercegrowthnewsletterbyloox

INSPIRATION 

15 Popular Videos from Brands, to Inspire​ https://www.practicalecommerce.com/15-popular-videos-from-brands-to-inspire

Watching popular videos from major brands can be a good way for small businesses to find out what works and generate their own campaign ideas. Here is a list of popular videos from big brands. Read the full article here https://www.practicalecommerce.com/15-popular-videos-from-brands-to-inspire

GLOBAL STRATEGY 

Ecommerce in Russia will grow 170% next five years https://ecommercenews.eu/ecommerce-in-russia-will-grow-170-next-five-years/

Ecommerce in Russia is showing an active growth. Last year, it was worth 13.7 billion euros and for this year it’s predicted to be worth 17 billion euros. And by 2023, the Russian ecommerce industry is predicted to grow to almost 46 billion euros. This would mean an increase of 170 percent in the next five years.  Read the full article here https://ecommercenews.eu/ecommerce-in-russia-will-grow-170-next-five-years/

Analysts agree: E-commerce sales set to deliver robust holiday retail growth https://marketingland.com/analysts-agree-e-commerce-sales-set-to-deliver-robust-holiday-retail-growth-249846

Deloitte forecasts up to a 22 percent increase in e-commerce sales, online sales are expected to reach $128 to $134 billion. ​ Read the full article here https://marketingland.com/analysts-agree-e-commerce-sales-set-to-deliver-robust-holiday-retail-growth-249846

CONVERSION RATE OPTIMIZATION 

6 CRO strategies that can help e-commerce entrepreneurs hit their sales goals https://born2invest.com/articles/6-cro-strategies-that-can-help-e-commerce-entrepreneurs-hit-their-sales-goals/

Cart abandonment is a threat to an entrepreneur’s sales targets, but that could be a thing of the past with these conversion rate optimization strategies. Read the full article here https://born2invest.com/articles/6-cro-strategies-that-can-help-e-commerce-entrepreneurs-hit-their-sales-goals/

4 Ways Dynamic Content Can Increase Ecommerce Conversions https://www.business2community.com/brandviews/upwork/4-ways-dynamic-content-can-increase-ecommerce-conversions-02130715

You cannot generate sales and increase ecommerce conversions just by having an ecommerce store. But fret not, you can use the power of dynamic content to boost your conversion rates. Read the full article here https://www.business2community.com/brandviews/upwork/4-ways-dynamic-content-can-increase-ecommerce-conversions-02130715

GROWTH

5 User Generated Content Secrets Revealed to Boost Your eCommerce Sales https://smallbiztrends.com/2018/10/user-generated-content-for-ecommerce.html

There are so many paid advertisements saturating websites and social media platforms that they are making users “immune” to their messages. Scrolling through social media, users recognize paid ads and largely decide to ignore them. On the contrast, user-generated content (UGC) is refreshing, and it beats stock photos and cookie cutter ads users see online Read the full article here https://smallbiztrends.com/2018/10/user-generated-content-for-ecommerce.html

How Walgreens’ Botanics beauty brand is using customers as influencers https://www.glossy.co/beauty/how-walgreens-botanics-beauty-brand-is-using-customers-as-influencers

Walgreens’ in-house, natural skin-care brand Botanics is taking a homegrown approach to its Instagram account by relying heavily on user-generated content.  Read the full article here https://www.glossy.co/beauty/how-walgreens-botanics-beauty-brand-is-using-customers-as-influencers

5 Ecommerce Secrets the 'Experts' Aren't Willing to Share With You https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/320656

As an expert in ecommerce with over 12 years of experience in this niche, I've learned firsthand that the success of your store depends on much more than having a quality product and a nice-looking website. Those basics are essential -- but every other ecommerce store will be doing the exact same thing. With that in mind, here are some of the ecommerce essentials I've learned over the years that can make all the difference for your store Read the full article here https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/320656

TOP TWEET

https://twitter.com/kurtinc/status/1051956897174175744

TOP VIDEO

0 to $1,000 in a Day: How to Build an Ecommerce Business That Could Make You Millions https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M0pX3XTE6uo

Enterpreneur newly launched series is here! In the first video $0 to $1,000, ecommerce expert Trevor Chapman chats about the type of site you need, the basics you must have before you launch and how to use email the right way.​

See the full video here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M0pX3XTE6uo

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M0pX3XTE6uo

Know someone who would enjoy this newsletter? Send them this link! http://loox.app/ecommerce-growth-newsletter

Thanks for your time, tune in again next week.

Yoni Elbaz, Co-founder & CEO at Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth5

Yoni from Loox

Har Sinai 2, Tel Aviv,

column4: The new way to boost sales - The Loox Popup
column6:
We just launched the new way to build strong trust with social proof that looks great

https://loox.io/app/nl_Popup

https://loox.io/app/nl_Popup

Hey,

Today we announce the launch of a new way to build strong trust with social proof that looks great - The Loox Popup!

When customers see that the product they are interested in is loved by others, they are much more likely to take action and make a purchase. As your customers browse through your store, The Loox Popup prominently displays reviews that are relevant to the specific page they are on.

https://loox.io/app/nl_Popup

Why Loox Popup

Context-aware

The Loox Popup only displays reviews that are relevant to the current page being viewed, maximizing click-through rates and conversions

On a product page - display reviews that are related to the product 
	On the cart page - display reviews related to items in the cart
	On other pages -  display high-rating reviews of all your products 

Highly Customizable 

Position - Choose which corner you’d like to have the Popup appear in 
	Rating - Define a minimum rating of reviews to display. You can only show 5-star reviews, if you’d like! 
	Duration - Configure the Popup display time, and the delay between Popups 
	Mobile - You can turn off the Loox Popup on mobile, if you wish

​The Loox Popup Widget combines the power of social proof, context awareness, relevance and a strong call to action; the perfect recipe to skyrocket your conversions.

Give it a try! The Loox Popup is available for free on all Loox plans.

Activate The Loox Popup https://loox.io/admin/track?NL_popup

column4:
Boost Your  Holiday Sales with Gift Finders,
 Shopify chargeback protection and more!
column6:
Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth4. 

TOP PICK 

Shopify launches new service to protect merchants from chargebacks https://techcrunch.com/2018/10/09/shopify-rolls-out-fraud-protection-to-u-s-merchants/

Large e-commerce businesses have systems in place to fight online fraud, but smaller sellers with their own storefronts don’t always have the same advantages. Today, e-commerce platform Shopify is aiming to change that with its rollout of Fraud Protect for Shopify Payments. The service is initially available in the U.S.  Read the full article here https://techcrunch.com/2018/10/09/shopify-rolls-out-fraud-protection-to-u-s-merchants/

STRATEGY 

An e-commerce pitfall: never-ending returns https://www.axios.com/ecommerce-retail-returns-loss-revolve-amazon-fe6d49b0-0f29-4f6b-8b15-f1ec0bae3621.html

Some of the biggest e-commerce businesses report staggering sales numbers — but huge pieces of that revenue often get erased in refunds to customers and shipping costs for returns. Customers returned $351 billion of all purchases — brick-and-mortar and online — in 2017, according to the National Retail Federation. That's about 10%!  Read the full article here https://www.axios.com/ecommerce-retail-returns-loss-revolve-amazon-fe6d49b0-0f29-4f6b-8b15-f1ec0bae3621.html

Google And Amazon's Competition Is A Win For Smaller E-Commerce Companies https://www.forbes.com/sites/nathanpettijohn/2018/09/20/google-and-amazons-competition-is-a-win-for-smaller-e-commerce-companies/#4de1d6cd314f

As the two Goliaths fight over e-commerce, small to medium-sized e-commerce companies have an opening. Here are a few of his insights as to how smaller companies can profit. Read the full article here https://www.forbes.com/sites/nathanpettijohn/2018/09/20/google-and-amazons-competition-is-a-win-for-smaller-e-commerce-companies/#4de1d6cd314f

Consumers Are Changing E-Commerce Preferences https://www.mhlnews.com/technology-automation/consumers-are-changing-e-commerce-preferences

Two years ago, customers wanted quality packaging and fast delivery, but now a "brand’s opportunity to reach, retain and extend customers’ lifetime value lies in giving them what they want, how and when they want it. The results of annual ecommerce survey are in! What really matters to consumers? Read the full article here https://www.mhlnews.com/technology-automation/consumers-are-changing-e-commerce-preferences

TIP OF THE WEEK 

Why live chat for business will be key for e-commerce in 2019 https://blog.freshchat.com/why-live-chat-for-business-is-key-for-e-commerce-in-2019/

Live chat for business is right on the cusp of skyrocketing — it’s seen early adopters succeed and changes in social behavior are hurtling it towards have-or-die status. But there is still time to get on board before a huge wave of consumers demand live chat for business from everyone. Read the full article https://blog.freshchat.com/why-live-chat-for-business-is-key-for-e-commerce-in-2019/

CONVERSION RATE OPTIMIZATION 

How To Boost Your 2018 E-Commerce Holiday Sales with Gift Finders https://www.business2community.com/ecommerce/how-to-boost-your-2018-e-commerce-holiday-sales-with-gift-finders-02116363 

It’s October, and you know what that means. The countdown to get your stores ready for the holiday season is on. Read the full article https://www.business2community.com/ecommerce/how-to-boost-your-2018-e-commerce-holiday-sales-with-gift-finders-02116363

GROWTH

The Top Three Books Every E-Commerce Store Owner Should Read First​ https://www.influencive.com/three-books-every-ecommerce-store-owner-should-read-first/

While some stores are able to gross millions in a matter of months while others never turn a profit, everyone wants to know what the magic ingredients are for success. These books provide a great source of advice for those getting into e-commerce.​ Read the full article here https://www.influencive.com/three-books-every-ecommerce-store-owner-should-read-first/

CUSTOMER EXPERIENCE

Key Considerations for Delivering Advanced Personalization in Ecommerce https://multichannelmerchant.com/blog/key-considerations-for-delivering-advanced-personalization-in-ecommerce/

Personalization is at the heart of many retailers’ business roadmaps, topping the list of business priorities for 2018, according to a recent report. But there’s no point embarking on a personalization strategy just because ‘everyone’s doing it’  Read the full article here https://multichannelmerchant.com/blog/key-considerations-for-delivering-advanced-personalization-in-ecommerce/

https://twitter.com/MikeQuindazzi/status/1049721500432035842

column4: What is a good ecom conversion rate, Snapchat ads rollout and more!
column6:
Ecommerce Growth Newsletter from Loox

The Weekly Ecommerce Growth newsletter from Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth3. 

TOP PICK 

Snapchat launches multiple e-commerce ad options in time for holiday shopping https://marketingland.com/snapchat-launches-multiple-e-commerce-ad-options-in-time-for-holiday-shopping-249063

Retail brands looking to reach teens, in particular, should take notice of Snapchat’s recent e-commerce efforts. Shoppable Snap ads are rolling out, and advertisers can now import catalogs to automatically create product ads. Read the full article here https://marketingland.com/snapchat-launches-multiple-e-commerce-ad-options-in-time-for-holiday-shopping-249063

STRATEGY 

Retargeting Customers: How Can You Reach Someone Who’s Not on Your Email List? https://www.shopify.com/blog/retargeting-previous-customers

Earning your first sale is hard, and while it may be easier to turn an existing customer into a repeat customer, that’s doesn’t mean it’s easy. Once someone has bought from your store for the first time, how can you keep their interest and earn the next sale?  Read the full article here https://www.shopify.com/blog/retargeting-previous-customers

TIP OF THE WEEK 

SEO: Understanding Sitemaps for Ecommerce Stores​ https://www.practicalecommerce.com/seo-understanding-sitemaps-for-ecommerce-stores

While sitemaps can be a simple text file listing the URLs of all of the pages you’d like to have indexed, they can also be an XML document carrying more information. Read the full article https://www.practicalecommerce.com/seo-understanding-sitemaps-for-ecommerce-stores

CONVERSION RATE OPTIMIZATION 

What is a good ecommerce conversion rate? https://econsultancy.com/what-good-ecommerce-conversion-rate-average/

Of course, the reality is full of nuance and variables, from sector to region to season to marketing channel mix to website traffic volume to website UX. But this range (1-3%) is broadly what’s seen in Econsultancy’s Performance Benchmarks tool. Read the full article https://econsultancy.com/what-good-ecommerce-conversion-rate-average/

How to make your ecommerce website more mobile friendly and drive conversions https://www.clickz.com/make-ecommerce-website-mobile-friendly-drive-conversions/216699/

Did you know that 30% of mobile shoppers will abandon a transaction if the experience is not optimized for mobile? This article shares six techniques ecommerce brands use to optimize their websites for mobile to improve conversions. Read the full article https://www.clickz.com/make-ecommerce-website-mobile-friendly-drive-conversions/216699/

GROWTH

Hiring for ecommerce, then and now https://www.practicalecommerce.com/hiring-for-ecommerce-then-and-now

What’s the best method for hiring ecommerce employees? Guys at FringeSport have struggled with the issue over the years. In this post, they describe their hiring process in detail. Read the full article https://www.practicalecommerce.com/hiring-for-ecommerce-then-and-now

Canadian Small Businesses that Leverage E-Commerce Grew 22 Per Cent in 2017 https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/canadian-small-businesses-that-leverage-e-commerce-grew-22-per-cent-in-2017-1027589703

Data from PayPal revelas that Canadian small- and medium-sized businesses leveraging e-commerce are growing significantly faster than their offline counterparts. Read the full article https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/canadian-small-businesses-that-leverage-e-commerce-grew-22-per-cent-in-2017-1027589703

CUSTOMER EXPERIENCE

How shipping options influence retail customer experience in e-commerce https://www.retailcustomerexperience.com/blogs/how-shipping-options-influence-retail-customer-experience-in-e-commerce/

It's not the sexiest part of your customer's experience, but order fulfillment is one of the most important encounters a customer will have with your brand and your product. You put a lot of thought into everything, from the CRM to connect with influencers to the targeted ads run on Facebook, and you should give equal consideration to how you ship to the people who keep you in business.   Read the full article here https://www.retailcustomerexperience.com/blogs/how-shipping-options-influence-retail-customer-experience-in-e-commerce/

TOP TWEET

https://twitter.com/schm7dt/status/1044615956029480962

TOP VIDEO

Content Creation Strategy For Ecommerce and Online Brands https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wShli2d-R7M

In this video, The Amazing Seller shares how you can take one piece of content and you can multiply it by three. You will be getting you more eyeballs on your content and also on your brand for a potential sale. See the  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wShli2d-R7Mfull video here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wShli2d-R7M

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wShli2d-R7M

Thanks for your time, tune in again next week.

Yoni Elbaz, Co-founder & CEO at Loox http://loox.io/app/NL_growth3

Yoni from Loox

When a rumor starts spreading that Beyoncé buys your luxury eyelash products “by the ton,” you know your business growth is about to explode … learn how Velour Lashes AOV  increased 12% YoY after testing Shopify’s ecommerce automation tools (Launchpad & Scripts). Read the full article here https://www.shopify.com/enterprise/velour-lashes-automates?utm_source=loox_newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=issue2

SOCIAL MEDIA MARKETING

Facebook expands mid-video ads to 21 more countries​ https://www.engadget.com/2018/09/25/facebook-ad-breaks-markets-languages/?utm_source=loox_newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=issue2

Facebook is bringing Ad Breaks (the ads you see in the middle of videos on the platform) to 21 more countries, with support for five more languages: French, German, Portuguese, Spanish and Thai. If you market to these 21 countries, this can be huge for you. Read the full article here https://www.engadget.com/2018/09/25/facebook-ad-breaks-markets-languages/?utm_source=loox_newsletter&utm_medium=ema

Facebook Messenger marketing and conversational commerce are blowing up, but the relatively short messages are proving to be an issue for many brands. Ensuring a message with only a fraction of the word count doesn’t lose its impact is no easy feat. Thankfully, guys at Recart have a few quick tips for you to massively increase the effectiveness of your Facebook Messenger marketing campaign. Read the full article here https://www.abetterlemonadestand.com/facebook-messenger-marketing/?utm_source=loox_newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=issue2

TIP OF THE WEEK 

How to Maximize eCommerce ROI Fast​ https://techspective.net/2018/09/25/how-to-maximize-ecommerce-roi-fast/?utm_source=loox_newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=issue2

Although it’s not impossible to start a business with no money, the old adage stating that “it takes money to make money” is genuine. Make it a point to invest in techniques to boost your revenue. Here’s a list of tasks that will be well worth your time. Read the full article here https://techspective.net/2018/09/25/how-to-maximize-ecommerce-roi-fast/?utm_source=loox_newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=issue2

CONVERSION RATE OPTIMIZATION 

Lots of traffic and no sales? Here is what to do https://www.storehacks.com/lots-traffic-no-sales/?utm_source=loox_newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=issue2

There are so many variables in eCommerce it is your job as a store owner to make sure you remove as many as possible. Here are the keys to getting that traffic converting from Shopify experts at storehacks. Read the full article https://www.storehacks.com/lots-traffic-no-sales/?utm_source=loox_newsletter&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=issue2

GROWTH

Don’t be a ‘one-click wonder’, ecommerce report warns Irish retailers​ https://www.irishtimes.com/business/media-and-marketing/don-t-be-a-one-click-wonder-ecommerce-report-warns-irish-retailers-1.3640105

Companies not doing enough to encourage repeat business. According to analysis of 250 million website sessions,  Wolfgang Digital discovered that the most successful Irish ecommerce retailers outshine their rivals at attracting return visits to their websites and are more likely to have had customers interact with their brands on social media. Are you guilty of prioritizing acquisition above retention? Make sure to read this article https://www.irishtimes.com/business/media-and-marketing/don-t-be-a-one-click-wonder-ecommerce-report-warns-irish-retailers-1.3640105
